This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for generating surface realizations from obfuscated text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses data augmentation techniques and sequence models, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions preprocessing techniques for input features, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision).
